[[["advmod", "aux", "nsubj", "xcomp", "mark", "dobj"], "Why do you need to learn English?"], [["aux", "neg", "nsubj", "xcomp", "mark", "dobj", "nmod:poss", "amod", "amod", "advcl", "mark", "mwe", "nmod", "case", "nmod:poss", "amod"], "Don't you want to read your favorite English novel instead of waiting for its Chinese translation?"], [["aux", "neg", "nsubj", "xcomp", "mark", "dobj", "det", "amod", "nmod", "case", "nmod", "case", "advmod", "nmod", "case", "det"], "Wouldn't you like to have a common means of communication with people anywhere in the world?"], [["advmod", "dobj", "advmod", "dep", "ccomp", "nsubj", "xcomp", "cc", "conj", "xcomp"], "Besides, using English well makes you feel good and look cool."], [["nsubj", "advcl", "advmod", "nsubj", "cop", "case", "det", "nummod", "compound", "compound", "nmod", "case", "det"], "That's why you are among the one billion English learners on this planet."], [["nsubj", "cop", "nmod", "case", "det", "amod", "advmod", "advmod", "nmod", "case", "det"], "English is one of the most commonly used languages in the world."], [["nsubj", "amod", "nmod", "case", "nmod:poss", "det", "case", "dobj", "nmod", "case", "det"], "Over one-third of the world's population speaks it to some degree."], [["nsubj", "advmod", "amod", "dobj", "nmod", "case", "det", "amod", "nmod", "case", "conj", "cc", "conj"], "About seventy-five countries use it as the major language of government, education, and business."], [["nsubj", "cop", "advmod", "det", "compound", "nummod", "amod", "nmod", "case", "nmod", "case", "det", "amod"], "English is also the number one foreign language in most of the other countries."], [["nsubj", "aux", "advmod", "dobj", "nmod", "case"], "We can hardly imagine life without English."], [["nsubj", "cop", "det", "amod", "nmod", "case", "conj", "det", "compound", "conj", "conj", "compound", "conj", "conj", "compound", "cc", "conj", "amod"], "English is the main language of books, the news media, sports, pop music, science, air-traffic control, and international business."], [["nsubj", "nmod", "case", "nmod:poss", "det", "case", "cop", "case", "cc", "conj", "nsubj", "amod", "nmod", "case", "det", "nmod", "case", "det", "cop", "advmod", "case"], "Three-quarters of the world's mail is in English, and ninety percent of the information on the Internet is also in English."], [["nmod", "case", "det", "amod", "advmod", "nsubj", "cop", "case", "amod", "advmod"], "As a widely used language, English is in fact very \"international.\""], [["nsubj", "aux", "dobj", "amod", "nmod", "case", "amod", "nmod", "case", "det"], "It has borrowed many words from other languages in the world."], [["ccomp", "nmod", "case", "nsubj", "nsubj", "cc", "conj", "cop", "case", "nmod", "compound", "compound", "cc", "case", "dep", "amod", "nmod", "compound", "compound", "cc", "case", "dep"], "For example, \"sugar,\" \"zero,\" \"coffee,\" and \"orange\" are from Arabic; \"banana,\" \"jazz,\" and \"zebra\" from African languages; \"tsunami,\" \"karaoke,\" and \"sushi\" from Japanese."], [["cc", "nmod", "case", "nsubj", "aux", "iobj", "det", "dobj", "cc", "conj"], "And from Chinese, we can find the words \"tea\" and \"ketchup.\""], [["advmod", "advcl", "mark", "nsubj", "xcomp", "mark", "nmod", "case", "det", "nsubj", "aux", "cop", "nmod:poss", "amod"], "Thus, if you want to connect with the world, English would be your best choice."], [["advcl", "mark", "nsubj", "det", "amod", "compound", "appos", "compound", "advmod", "nsubj", "aux", "neg", "dobj", "amod", "advcl", "mark", "dobj", "det", "parataxis", "nsubj", "dobj"], "As a famous language researcher, David Crystal, once said, \"You don't need long arms to embrace the world; you need English.\""]]